Strings:

sequence of Unicode  characters

example = "Karthick"

example[0] is K -> we can access like that
len(example) -> gives size


negative indexing :

last character can be accessed by -1,-2,-3

String Slicing- substring:

example[strt index : endindex+1]- given the substr


example[1,3] -- returns 

example[strt index : endindex+1 : step size]-

step size is default 1 


reversing a string

str =str[::-1]
Methods in string
.lower()
.upper()
.title() -> capitalizes first character of each word
.find("set") - > returns the index in string, can give start location also , as second param returns -1 if not exists
.split('t')-> splits the word based on given char default it is space
.count('o') -> returns the count of occurances
.replace('find', 'replacement')
.lstrip(), .rstrip() -> removes white spaces
. and shift shows the use of function
all returns does not store anything


